OL,6,FHe told Media Scotland: "I find it
OL,7,Fextraordinary, in an age when we are
OL,8,Fencouraged to talk to each other, that
OL,9,Fthe team didn't think it important to
OL,10,Fcome and talk to us, or even lift the
OL,11,Fphone.
OL,13,F"They took into account only whatever
OL,14,Fthey had on paper which had been
OL,15,Fwritten beforehand, which is quite
OL,16,Ffrankly perplexing.
OL,18,F"The church is not just a religious
OL,19,Fbuilding ` it's a base for the
OL,20,Fcommunity, for baptisms, funerals and
OL,21,Fevents.
